  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Evidence-Based Multi-Sectoral Emergency Assistance to Affected People in Bamingui-Bangoran Prefecture</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The prefecture of Bamingui-Bangoran (N&apos;dele) in the Central African Republic has experienced some of the worst forms of inter- and intra-community tensions since the post-election period, which has led to increased vulnerability of the populations concerned. As a result, the civilian population is not only victimized by crime and violence, including gender-based violence, but has also been largely deprived of their means of economic production. In addition, the disruptive action of armed groups and the problem of resource management, during major transhumance movements, lead to agro-pastoral conflicts and population displacements. Through this project, IOM plans to strengthen the collection, analysis and sharing of data on displaced, returning and transhumant populations in the Bamingui-Bangoran prefecture, through the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM). Additionally, IOM is providing integrated emergency assistance to ensure the survival and dignity of the affected population through the provision of mental health and psychosocial support services and the strengthening of the capacity of local actors to respond in the long term.</narrative>
  </description>
